librgs
------------------------------------------
An easy to use 2d game engine that provides a framework for creating old
console-like games.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libSDL1.2_0-1.2.15-3
  librgs-devel-0.9.0+git20120424-1bl3
  librgs0-0.9.0+git20120424-1bl3
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libSDL-devel-1.2.15-3
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/ivansafrin/librgs

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/ivansafrin/librgs.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack librgs-0.9.0+git20120424-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./librgs-0.9.0+git20120424-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/librgs-0.9.0+git20120424-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librgs-0.9.0+git20120424-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librgs0-0.9.0+git20120424-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librgs-devel-0.9.0+git20120424-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

